==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Therein
<hw>There*in"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In that or this
place, time, or thing; in that particular or respect.</def>
<rj><au>Wyclif.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He pricketh through a fair forest,⟦br⟧
<qex>Therein</qex> is many a wild beast.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Bring forth abundantly in the earth, and multiply
<qex>therein</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Gen. ix. 7.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Therein</qex> our letters do not well agree.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thereinto</ent>⟦br⟧
